g metric_analysis_tool reveals some interesting patterns in the p99 values:\n- frontend-0: error_ratio p99 of 43.59, server_error_ratio p99 of 43.59\n- frontend-1: error_ratio p99 of 41.5, server_error_ratio p99 of 41.5  \n- frontend-2: error_ratio p99 of 35.08, server_error_ratio p99 of 35.08\n\nThis suggests that while the median error ratios were 0.0 (indicating most requests succeeded), there were occasional spikes in errors at the 99th percentile level.\n\n## Dependency on Shippingservice\n\nThe metric analysis shows clear evidence of dependency between frontend and shippingservice:\n\n1. **Correlated Error Patterns**: Both frontend pods and shippingservice pods show elevated p99 error ratios during the same time period\n   - shippingservice-0: error_ratio p99 of 1.33, client_error_ratio p99 of 1.33\n   - shippingservice-1: error_ratio p99 of 62.0, client_error_ratio p99 of 62.0\n   - shippingservice-2: error_ratio p99 of 63.16, client_error_ratio p99 of 63.16\n\n2. **Response Time Correlation**: Both services show abnormal response time patterns:\n   - Frontend RRT p99 values are extremely high (26M+ nanoseconds, which is ~26 seconds)\n   - Shippingservice also shows elevated RRT_max values\n\n3. **Architecture Pattern**: In typical microservice architectures, the frontend service depends on backend services like shippingservice to fulfill requests. When shippingservice experiences issues, it can cause the frontend to either:\n   - Return errors (if proper error handling is implemented)\n   - Experience timeouts (leading to high response times)\n\nThe fact that frontend shows high p99 response times (up to 26 seconds) while maintaining 0.0 median error ratios suggests that the frontend is experiencing **timeouts** when calling shippingservice, rather than immediately returning errors.\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe frontend pods (frontend-0, frontend-1, frontend-2) show **no persistent errors** (median error_ratio = 0.0) but exhibit **very high response times** at the 99th percentile. This strongly indicates a **dependency issue with shippingservice**, which shows significant error rates at the p99 level (62-63% for shippingservice-1 and -2). The frontend is likely waiting for responses from shippingservice before timing out, which explains the high response times without corresponding high error rates in the median metrics."}
